From bc34070ac52e543efa2fccdbc25dd7082b691de6 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Johannes Schauer Marin Rodrigues <josch@mister-muffin.de>
Date: Fri, 27 Mar 2026 22:46:15 +0100
Subject: [PATCH] Revert "lpc: add apiv3 support with checksumming, filter some
 noise when fully charged on AC"

This reverts commit 0ee1032fce1995099a50ec669482cdf52247a9ba.

This causes regressions like:

 * LPC errors flooding the kernel log

Mar 27 17:50:34 reform kernel: power_supply BAT0: driver failed to report `status' property: -16
Mar 27 17:50:34 reform kernel: reform2_lpc spi1.0: lpc_command: c/0 checksum mismatch: af expected, 0 received.
Mar 27 17:50:34 reform kernel: power_supply BAT0: driver failed to report `charge_now' property: -16
Mar 27 17:50:34 reform kernel: reform2_lpc spi1.0: lpc_command: q/0 checksum mismatch: 7b expected, 0 received.
Mar 27 17:50:38 reform kernel: power_supply_format_property: 7 callbacks suppressed

https://community.mnt.re/t/lpc-errors-flooding-the-kernel-log/4295

 * The SWAY bar fluctuates between 0% and 100% battery charge every minute.
 * The OLED display always shows 100% battery charge (even after 2 hours of use).
 * The laptop shuts down without warning.

https://community.mnt.re/t/battery-indicator-after-update-upgrade-and-shutdown/4298
---
 lpc/reform2_lpc.c | 131 ++++++++++++++++------------------------------
 1 file changed, 44 insertions(+), 87 deletions(-)

diff --git a/lpc/reform2_lpc.c b/lpc/reform2_lpc.c
index 7a9c986..0977db8 100644
--- a/lpc/reform2_lpc.c
+++ b/lpc/reform2_lpc.c
@@ -3,27 +3,25 @@
